      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic titanium alloy constitutive model appropriate for sub-yield regime; bilinear plasticity model applied for post-yield prediction. Model form assumptions documented and justified relative to observed experimental failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening. UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate modeled as linear elastic within the load range of interest. Contact between screw and rod modeled with frictional contact (mu=0.2). Model form selection justified by comparison to published material characterization data and observed experimental failure modes (rod bending, not screw fracture)."
