      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 production-representative specimens tested across two independent laboratories; specimens drawn from same production lot as commercial device.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested: six at Laboratory 1 and five at Laboratory 2. All specimens drawn from the same commercial production lot, representative of the cleared device design. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at the Medium credibility level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions should span clinically relevant range of loading configurations; minimum two load levels or fixture configurations required for Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at 10 mm anterior offset. Only one load condition evaluated, limiting coverage of the full clinical loading envelope. This factor is below the required level; the shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given that F1717 is the regulatory standard configuration and direct comparison to the predicate device test data at the same condition provides adequate contextual support for the Medium assurance level decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters traceable to physical test specimen measurements; any deviations between nominal and measured values quantified and within 5%.",
      "rationale": "Geometric and material inputs mapped directly to CMM and mill test report data for each specimen. Maximum deviation between nominal model inputs and specimen-specific measurements was 3.1% for rod diameter and 2.4% for fixation depth. Input equivalency confirmed for all 11 specimens prior to QoI comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval applied; acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs. Percent difference acceptance bound <10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval metric computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement following ASME V&V 40 Appendix guidance. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% thresholds across both laboratories. Stiffness: E/uval=0.81 (Lab1), 1.02 (Lab2). Yield force: E/uval=1.44 (Lab1). Force at 40 mm: E/uval=0.63 (combined)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
