      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly linked to clinical performance endpoints and regulatory submission requirements under ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary mechanical performance indicators for pedicle screw systems under F1717. Force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue endurance assessment. All three QoIs are directly referenced in the FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions and are mechanistically linked to the clinical risk of construct failure requiring revision surgery."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
